* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
* B1700 MIL Test Program 3 — Memory Read/Write
* Tests: LIT, MOVE, WRITE BITS, READ BITS, memory addressing
* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
*
* Write a 24-bit value to memory, then read it back.
*
* Expected result: T = HABCDEF (original)
*                  FA → points to bit address where we wrote
*                  After read: Y = HABCDEF (read back from memory)
*

DEFINE DATA_ADDR _ H001000

START       CLEAR FA                      * FA ← 0
            LIT H10 TO FA                 * FA ← 0x10 (bit addr 16)
            LIT HAB TO X                  * X ← 0xAB
            WRITE 8 BITS FROM X           * write X[7:0] to memory at FA
            LIT HCD TO X                  * X ← 0xCD
            WRITE 8 BITS FROM X INC FA    * write, inc FA by 8
            LIT HEF TO X                  * X ← 0xEF
            WRITE 8 BITS FROM X INC FA    * write, inc FA by 8

*           Now read it back
            LIT H10 TO FA                 * FA ← starting address
            READ 24 BITS TO Y             * Y ← 24 bits from memory at FA
            HALT
